The hills are like a verdant sea, 
With waves of rolling green; 
And in the breeze, the gentle leaves, 
Dance softly, like a dream.

For nature sings a song divine, 
That lifts the weary heart; 
In every note and every line, 
The beauty plays its part.

- Christopher Pearse Cranch
